on 5 october 2000 on a reference from the federal race discrimination commission or to the human rights and equal opportunity commission, the inquiry commissioner determined that the respondent had engaged in conduct rendered unlawful by s 18c of the racial discrimination act 1975 (cth) (the racial discrimination act ) by publishing on a website material racially vilifactory of jewish people and ordered the respondent to remove the website from the world wide web.